## Usage Verification

```bash
# Clone and test
git clone --single-branch --branch claude/elnx-simple-gdoVV \
  https://github.com/Naivedya-sahu/Elxnk.git

cd Elxnk/Elnx-simple

# Verify setup
./setup.sh
# ✅ Setup Complete!

# Test locally (no reMarkable needed)
./test_local.sh
# ✅ All Local Tests Passed!

# Deploy lamp (one-time, requires ARM toolchain)
cd lamp
make          # Compile for ARM
make deploy   # Deploy to reMarkable 2
make test     # Verify lamp works
cd ..

# Draw components via WiFi
export RM2_HOST=10.11.99.1
./scripts/draw_component.sh R 700 900 1.5
./scripts/draw_text.sh "Hello" 500 500 1.0
./scripts/draw_circuit.sh
```

## Error Handling Examples

### Invalid input:
```bash
$ ./scripts/draw_component.sh R abc 400 1.0
Error: X coordinate must be a number, got: abc
```

### Connection failure:
```bash
$ ./scripts/draw_component.sh R 500 400 1.0
Error: Cannot connect to reMarkable 2 at 10.11.99.1

Troubleshooting:
  1. Check IP address: ping 10.11.99.1
  2. Test SSH: ssh root@10.11.99.1
  3. Set correct IP: export RM2_HOST=your.ip.address
  4. Or use --host option
```

### Missing component:
```bash
$ ./bin/render_json.py component INVALID 500 400
Error: Component 'INVALID' not found
```

All error messages are clear, actionable, and user-friendly.

